SeriesDescription: Proportion of women of reproductive age (aged 15-49 years) who have their need for family planning satisfied with modern methods (% of women aged 15-49 years)
Source: Ecuador 2004 Encuesta Demográfica y de Salud Materna e Infantil
FootNote: The global indicator represents all women of reproductive age. This survey estimate represents women who are married or in a union. Unmet need data pertain to fecund married women, currently sexually active, currently exposed to the risk of pregnancy, not wanting to become pregnant, and not using a method of contraception other than folk methods, douches, breastfeeding or lactational amenorrhea (LAM). Unmet need data exclude women who are currently pregnant, currently seeking to become pregnant, subfecund, or who are not sexually active, including women practicing post-partum abstinence.
